    {
        "user": "UCUSW7WVD",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1645841741.919219",
        "client_msg_id": "b99d3e19-2527-4482-b562-88c4bf5a453f",
        "text": "There's a common failure mode here shared by both conventional programmers and no-code: the gradual tendency to use tools beyond their acceptable ranges of tolerance. A programmer using a thousand-line shell script for a business-critical workflow exhibits the same failure mode. I'm not immune to it, and I'm not sure how to avoid it except constant vigilance :confused:",
